    "heading_text": "Query parameter list / multiple values",
    "anchor_id": "query-parameter-list-multiple-values",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/query-params-str-validations/#query-parameter-list-multiple-values",
    "section_text": "When you define a query parameter explicitly with Query you can also declare it to receive a list of values, or said in another way, to receive multiple values.\n\nFor example, to declare a query parameter q that can appear multiple times in the URL, you can write:\n\nThen, with a URL like:\n\nyou would receive the multiple q query parameters' values ( foo and bar ) in a Python list inside your path operation function , in the function parameter q .\n\nSo, the response to that URL would be:\n\nThe interactive API docs will update accordingly, to allow multiple values:",
