  "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0024": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0024",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0022",
    "level": 4,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "A Random Item",
    "anchor_id": "a-random-item",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/query-params-str-validations/#a-random-item",
    "section_text": "With data.items() we get an iterable object with tuples containing the key and value for each dictionary item.\n\nWe convert this iterable object into a proper list with list(data.items()) .\n\nThen with random.choice() we can get a random value from the list, so, we get a tuple with (id, name) . It will be something like (\"imdb-tt0371724\", \"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy\") .\n\nThen we assign those two values of the tuple to the variables id and name .\n\nSo, if the user didn't provide an item ID, they will still receive a random suggestion.\n\n...we do all this in a single simple line . 🤯 Don't you love Python? 🐍",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "data.items()",
      "list",
      "list(data.items())",
      "random.choice()",
      "(id, name)",
      "(\"imdb-tt0371724\", \"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy\")",
      "id",
      "name"
    ],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [
      {
        "type": "code_ref",
        "path": "../../docs_src/query_params_str_validations/tutorial015_an_py310.py",
        "highlight_lines": [
          29
        ],
        "raw": "{* ../../docs_src/query_params_str_validations/tutorial015_an_py310.py ln[22:30] hl[29] *}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0024",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/query-params-str-validations/#a-random-item"
      }
    ],
    "code_blocks": []
  },
  "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0025": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0025",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/query-params-str-validations::section-0001",
    "level": 2,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Recap",
    "anchor_id": "recap",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/query-params-str-validations/#recap",
    "section_text": "You can declare additional validations and metadata for your parameters.\n\nGeneric validations and metadata:\n\n- alias\n\n- title\n\n- description\n\n- deprecated\n\nValidations specific for strings:\n\n- min_length\n\n- max_length\n\n- pattern\n\nCustom validations using AfterValidator .\n\nIn these examples you saw how to declare validations for str values.\n\nSee the next chapters to learn how to declare validations for other types, like numbers.",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "alias",
      "title",
      "description",
      "deprecated",
      "min_length",
      "max_length",
      "pattern",
      "AfterValidator",
      "str"
    ],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [],
    "code_blocks": []
  }
